d 'SURVEYCLUSTER': module to calculate sample size for cluster-based surveys to achieve desired precision
d
d  surveycluster calculates the required sample size and number of
d clusters for single-arm surveys with nested data where the goal
d is to estimate a population mean with specified precision (margin
d of error). Unlike clustersampsi which is designed for cluster
d randomized controlled trials comparing two groups, surveycluster
d focuses on achieving desired precision for estimating a single
d population parameter. The command accounts for design effects due
d to clustering, applies finite population correction when
d relevant, and reports both the requested and actual margin of
d error achieved. 
d
d KW: sample size
d KW: clusters
d KW: surveys
d
d Requires: Stata version 12
d
d Distribution-Date: 20250823
d
d Author:   Kabira Namit,  World Bank
d Support: email   knamit@@worldbank.org
d
d Author: Cooper Allton,   Samaritan's Purse
d Support: email NA
d
f surveycluster.ado
f surveycluster.sthlp
